Name: Perfect Pop Songs
Description: Songs that are 3 minutes or under.

Name: Better Than The Original
Description: Cover songs that are better than the original version.

Name: Magic Numbers
Description: Songs with a number in the title.

Name: A Word is Enough
Description: Songs with a one word title.

Name: One Hit Wonders
Description: Too many of you have been moaning to me about this, so I'll change it slightly again. Songs must have been top 5 in the UK and the artist/band must not have another song that has made top 20 in the UK singles chart.

Name: Santa Claus is Comin' to Town
Description: Christmas songs.

Name: TV Theme Tunes
Description: The best TV theme songs of all time.

Name: At the Movies
Description: Songs that were written/recorded for movie soundtracks

Name: The 27 Club
Description: Songs by artists who died young (this can be anyone of 27 or younger, not just the 27 club) and can include bands including members who died 27 or younger (but obviously only songs that they were involved in).

Name: I'm Blue
Description: Go-to songs when you are feeling down.

Name: Cheesy 90s Bangers!
Description: Pop hits from the 1990s. The type of 'pop' half of you thought the first round should solely be. Cranks.

Name: Match of the Day
Description: Songs about sport or that are connected to sports events/coverage.

Name: No Words Needed
Description: Instrumental songs.

Name: Duets
Description: The best duets of all time (solo artists only, not two bands singing together or one singer guesting with a band).

Name: Space Quest
Description: Songs about space.

Name: What's Your Jam?
Description: Choose one song that you've recently been obsessed with and one song that is one of your all-time favourites.

Name: Double Threat!
Description: Pick one song by a musician turned actor and one song by an actor turned musician.

Name: Songs of the Sea
Description: Songs about water.

Name: Hit the Highway
Description: Songs about driving.

Name: This is the End
Description: Break-up songs.
